{
  "texts": [
    "Keeping in mind the open question about how to choose between a narrow and broad conception of appropriateness, there is room to let design considerations about which conception of manipulation is implementable have weight in the choice of conceptualisation.",
    "The question about picking suitable conceptualisations of manipulation is closely linked to the question of how to ensure that generative AI systems are aligned with the criteria in such a way that they do not generate manipulative content.",
    "Following Gabriel (2020), the identification of reliable criteria for manipulation would answer one part of the alignment question.",
    "The question about implementation, however, would remain open.",
    "Plausibly, as van de Poel (2020) suggests, there would need to be prolonged attention to the system after the initial design stage."
  ]
}